The paper deals with parallel algorithms for graph connectivity and related problems, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also introduces new algorithmic ideas and techniques, which could be of interest to researchers in Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Networked Systems (cs.NE), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories.
